-- Loud explosions heard in rebel stronghold Donetsk in east Ukraine- witness
-- 
-- Mon Jul 21, 2014 02:35AM EDT
-- None



DONETSK, Ukraine, July 21 (Reuters) - Loud explosions were heard in the centre of the eastern Ukrainian city of Donetsk on Monday, a Reuters witness said.

Donetsk is at the heart of a rebel uprising against rule by  Kiev and Ukrainian President Petro Poroshenko has vowed to retake the city as part of what Kiev calls its "anti-terrorist operation" against the separatists.